{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_monitor_get()"},{"type":"text","text":" to get a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" and connect"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor::changed"},{"type":"text","text":" signal. The signal will be emitted once when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app info database changes, and will not be emitted again until after the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"next call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_all()"},{"type":"text","text":" or another "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_*()"},{"type":"text","text":" function. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is because monitoring the app info database for changes is expensive."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following functions will re-arm the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor::changed"},{"type":"text","text":" signal so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it can be emitted again:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_all()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_all_for_type()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_default_for_type()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_fallback_for_type()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_get_recommended_for_type()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_desktop_app_info_get_implementations()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_desktop_app_info_new()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_desktop_app_info_new_from_filename()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_desktop_app_info_new_from_keyfile()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_desktop_app_info_search()"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the usual case, applications should try to make note of the change"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(doing things like invalidating caches) but not act on it.  In"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular, applications should avoid making calls to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in response to the change signal, deferring these until the time that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the updated data is actually required.  The exception to this case is when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application information is actually being displayed on the screen"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(for example, during a search or when the list of all applications is shown)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The reason for this is that changes to the list of installed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applications often come in groups (like during system updates) and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rescanning the list on every change is pointless and expensive."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppInfoMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppInfoMonitorRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/appinfomonitorprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitor","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" is a very simple object used for monitoring the app"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"info database for changes (newly installed or removed applications)."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{